    "body": "check your chain's configured block gas limit.  The transaction example you are using has a gas limit of 5,390,000 gas.  If your chain is configured with a lower block gas limit, that would be why it fails.\r\n\r\nyou can see the current block gas limit by getting the latest block and looking at `gasLimit`.\r\n\r\nuse this curl (or postman) to query the latest block:\r\n```\r\ncurl --location 'http://localhost:8545' \\\r\n--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n--data '{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"method\": \"eth_getBlockByNumber\",\r\n    \"params\": [\r\n        \"latest\",\r\n        false\r\n    ],\r\n    \"id\": 1\r\n}'\r\n```\r\n\r\nby the way, the #besu channel on hyperledger discord is a better place for these kinds of questions rather than submitting github issues.",
